1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,650
Most important of all, he gives himself an opportunity to show he has special ability and ambition by volunteering.
2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:12,211
By all means, volunteer for those special assignments.
3
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:18,851
Think about the leaders you know in business, the military, your community.
4
00:00:19,040 --> 00:00:24,851
Do they fit the description of activationists, or would you say they are passivationists?
5
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:30,530
Ten times out of ten, they're activationists, people who do things.
6
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:36,291
The fellow who stands on the sidelines, who holds off, who is passive, does not lead.
7
00:00:36,480 --> 00:00:41,811
But the doer, the fellow who thinks action, finds others want to follow him.
8
00:00:42,560 --> 00:00:45,891
People place confidence in the fellow who acts.
9
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:49,170
They naturally assume he knows what he is doing.
10
00:00:49,840 --> 00:00:55,411
I've never heard anyone complimented and praised because he doesn't disturb anyone,
11
00:00:55,520 --> 00:01:00,451
he doesn't take action, or he waits until he's told what to do.
12
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:01,731
Have you?
13
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,130
Grow the action habit.
14
00:01:06,320 --> 00:01:08,371
Practice these key points.
